  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water Resource Mapping in Samburu County and East Pokot District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Sensitization workshop to sensitize the end users before the implementation of a new technology to drastically enhance the sense of ownership and therefore the chance of success of the project.
2. Training of Assessment Team on the objectives of the data collection, content of the questionnaire, and how to use the phone device for data collection purposes. 
3. Mapping and survey which involved collecting information on geographic location (GPS coordinates) of water points and filling in a survey form accessed through the Nokia phone data gathering software application detailing the name of the water point, the nearest settlement, the type of water source, the extraction system, energy source and hand pump type (where applicable), and information on operations, ownership, maintenance and management.This information were then used to produce an interactive web map as well as map books for the targeted districts.
4. Dissemination workshop to disseminate the results, answer any remaining questions and encourage networking and group-work regarding data use by organizations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mapping of water points in Samburu East, Samburu Central, Samburu North and East Pokot Districts to contribute to enhanced knowledge, development and management of current and future water resources to ensure improved access to water in the targeted districts.</narrative>
  </description>
